Igor Ranitovic wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; I think that it will be OK, but I am not sure where the breaking point
&gt; is :) Maybe running a test crawl is a good idea.
&gt; 
&gt; If you want to write a new decide rule you can subclass the
&gt; SurtPrefixedDecideRule and override the &#39;evaluate&#39; method.
&gt; 
&gt; Maybe something like this (not tested):
&gt; 
&gt; protected boolean evaluate(Object object) {
&gt; if ( (object instanceof CandidateURI) &&
&gt; ((Boolean) getUncheckedAttribute(null, ATTR_ALSO_CHECK_VIA))
&gt; .booleanValue()) {
&gt; if(evaluate(((CandidateURI)object).getVia())) {
&gt; return true;
&gt; }
&gt; }
&gt; String candidateSurt;
&gt; candidateSurt = SurtPrefixSet.getCandidateSurt(object);
&gt; 
&gt; // Drop everything after the last &#39;/&#39;
&gt; candidateSurt = candidateSurt.replaceFirst(&quot;^(.*/)[^/]*$&quot;, &quot;$1&quot;);
&gt; 
&gt; if (candidateSurt == null) {
&gt; return false;
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; // Check if we have exact match
&gt; return getPrefixes().contains(candidateSurt);
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; Take care,
&gt; i.
&gt; 
&gt; Travis Jensen wrote:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Hi,
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Thanks for your reply, Igor.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Would this still be a preferred way if I have 1500 of these URLs? I
&gt;  &gt; would worry about the performance hit of every crawled URL needing to go
&gt;  &gt; through an average of 750 regex matches to find the one that will match.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; tj
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; -----Original Message-----
&gt;  &gt; From: archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;
&gt;  &gt; [mailto:archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;] On Behalf Of Igor Ranitovic
&gt;  &gt; Sent: Friday, January 18, 2008 12:26 PM
&gt;  &gt; To: archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;
&gt;  &gt; Subject: Re: [archive-crawler] Best approach question
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; I don&#39;t think that you need to run separate jobs for each seed.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; For example, is you have two seeds as:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; http://www.foo.com/baz/bar2.html &lt;http://www.foo.com/baz/bar2.html&gt;
&gt;  &gt; http://www.foo.com/zab/bar2.html &lt;http://www.foo.com/zab/bar2.html&gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; you can have scope as:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; +http://www.foo.com/baz/bar2.html &lt;http://www.foo.com/baz/bar2.html&gt;
&gt;  &gt; +http://www.foo.com/zab/bar2.html &lt;http://www.foo.com/zab/bar2.html&gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; and this decide rule:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;newObject name=&quot;seedsCurrentFolderOnly&quot;
&gt;  &gt; class=&quot;org.archive.crawler.deciderules.MatchesListRegExpDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;string name=&quot;decision&quot;&gt;REJECT&lt;/string&gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;string name=&quot;list-logic&quot;&gt;OR&lt;/string&gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;stringList name=&quot;regexp-list&quot;&gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;string&gt;(?i)http://www.foo.com/baz/.*/ 
&gt; &lt;http://www.foo.com/baz/.*/&gt;&lt;/string&gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;string&gt;(?i)http://www.foo.com/zab/.*/ 
&gt; &lt;http://www.foo.com/zab/.*/&gt;&lt;/string&gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;/stringList&gt;
&gt;  &gt; &lt;/newObject&gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Creating the scope and MatchesListRegExpDecideRule can be done easily
&gt;  &gt; with little scripting.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; I hope this helps.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Take care,
&gt;  &gt; i.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Travis Jensen wrote:
&gt;  &gt;&gt; Hi,
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; I&#39;m looking for some feedback as to a best approach to a crawling
&gt;  &gt;&gt; problem I need solve. I have a list of URLs, some of which I only
&gt;  &gt; want
&gt;  &gt;&gt; to crawl that URL, some of which I want to crawl that whole domain
&gt;  &gt;&gt; (&quot;foo.com&quot;), some I want to crawl only that server (&quot;www.foo.com&quot;),
&gt;  &gt; some
&gt;  &gt;&gt; I want to crawl anything below the given URL, and some I want to crawl
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; everything in the URL&#39;s folder.
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; The first four are out-of-the-box from my understanding of Heritrix 2,
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; which is great. The last one doesn&#39;t seem to be, so I&#39;ve been looking
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; at options on how to implement it. Just to clearly define the
&gt;  &gt; problem,
&gt;  &gt;&gt; if I&#39;m given a seed URL of:
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; http://www.foo.com/baz/bar.html &lt;http://www.foo.com/baz/bar.html&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; then I want to match:
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; http://www.foo.com/baz/bar2.html, &lt;http://www.foo.com/baz/bar2.html,&gt;
&gt;  &gt; http://www.foo.com/baz/somethingelse.html 
&gt; &lt;http://www.foo.com/baz/somethingelse.html&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; but I don&#39;t want to match:
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; http://www.foo.com/apage.html, &lt;http://www.foo.com/apage.html,&gt;
&gt;  &gt; http://www.foo.com/baz/bang/anotherpage.html 
&gt; &lt;http://www.foo.com/baz/bang/anotherpage.html&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; The two methods I&#39;ve found to do this would be to define a regex of
&gt;  &gt; the
&gt;  &gt;&gt; matching URL and use a MatchesRegExpDecideRule or to create my own
&gt;  &gt;&gt; DecideRule (call it FolderOnlyDecideRule).
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; If I use the MatchesRegExpDecideRule, will I have to create a
&gt;  &gt; different
&gt;  &gt;&gt; job for each seed URL (because the regex will be different)? Or is it
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; possible to say &quot;this job uses this seed URL with this regex&quot;?
&gt;  &gt; Dealing
&gt;  &gt;&gt; with a different job for each URL seems painful.
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; If the FolderOnlyDecideRule is the way to go, can I get some pointers
&gt;  &gt; on
&gt;  &gt;&gt; how to go about implementing it. I&#39;ve been looking through the
&gt;  &gt;&gt; DecideRules and it hasn&#39;t &quot;clicked&quot; yet. :)
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt;
&gt;  &gt;&gt; Thanks.
